name: I ❤ Gluten - Tote Bag
description:
This is a hand made designer tote bag

We made this because We love Gluten. 

We despise silly diet fads that deny people the joys of bread, cake and breakfast cereal. Bread is awesome. Making bread civilised mankind. Not eating bread makes you a savage.

Take a stand and show your pride in gluten. 


Designs are printed on a cotton linen blend towel that is a generous 70cm x 50cm (27 x 19 inches).

name: Look Ma! No Hands!   Clock
description:
Probably the most awesome clock ever made. We know that is a big call, but.....

This is an analogue clock with no hands. We came up with this after setting a challenge to make a clock different, but still functional.

What we came up with is something that is beautiful and following the modern tradition of simple lines. It is almost more of an art-piece than a clock.

Speaking of which.  Have a look at it. Can you work out how it keeps time?

The answer is below if you really want it.










The trick to this clock is that it has no minute hand. The hour is represented by the cut-out, and floats around the clock face. When it is above the 12, you know its 12. If it is halfway between the two and three, you know its 2:30. 

After a short while you get to the point where you judge the time down to five minutes.

name: You Are Here - Tea towel
description:
Drying dishes sucks. If you have to do it, at least smile. With this awesome tea-towel you can pretend that drying dishes is as exciting as shopping in your local mega-mall! 

Well maybe that isn't true, but we think this tea towel is pretty funny.


Designs are printed on a cotton linen blend towel that is a generous 70cm x 50cm (27 x 19 inches).

name: Crazy flock of crazy flamingos tea towel
description:
Growing up we loved Dr Seuss books and we used to play game where we would try to find real animals that are so weird that they could be from the imagination of Dr Seuss. 

Like Flamingos.

Flamingos have to be one of the strangest creatures in the history of world. The colours, that long neck, the bill that is so large it looks like it doesn't belong.

Anyway, flamingos are cool.


Designs are printed on a cotton linen blend towel that is a generous 70cm x 50cm (27 x 19 inches).
